# Frontend UI Components & Models

## Base UI Components
**CRITICAL**: Use Base UI components before creating custom ones.

```javascript
import { Badge, Button, Card, Checkbox, Dialog, Input, Label, Select, Switch, Tabs, Textarea, Skeleton } from '@base-framework/ui/atoms';
import { Avatar, StaticStatusIndicator, StatusIndicator, TimeFrame, EmptyState } from '@base-framework/ui/molecules';
import { ScrollableList, ScrollableDataTable, DynamicDataTable } from "@base-framework/ui/organisms";
import { CheckboxCol, HeaderCol } from "@base-framework/ui/organisms";
```

## Avatar (CRITICAL)
**ALWAYS use Base UI `Avatar` from `@base-framework/ui/molecules`**. NEVER build custom avatars with raw `Img`/`Div`.

```javascript
import { Avatar } from '@base-framework/ui/molecules';

Avatar({ src: user.avatar, alt: user.name, fallbackText: 'CN', size: 'md' })

// Reactive watcher fallback (converts name to initials automatically)
Avatar({ src: '[[user.image]]', alt: '[[user.name]]', watcherFallback: '[[user.name]]', size: 'sm' })
```

**Sizes**: `xs`, `sm`, `md` (default), `lg`, `xl`, `2xl`, `3xl`

**Status Indicators**:
```javascript
import { StaticStatusIndicator, StatusIndicator } from '@base-framework/ui/molecules';

// Static (fixed status)
Div({ class: 'relative' }, [
    Avatar({ src: url, alt: name, size: 'md' }),
    StaticStatusIndicator('online')  // 'online'|'offline'|'busy'|'away'
])

// Reactive (binds to parent status state/data key)
Div({ class: 'relative', addState() { return { status: 'online' }; } }, [
    Avatar({ src: url, alt: name, size: 'md' }),
    StatusIndicator()
])
```

## TimeFrame
Shows relative time that auto-updates:
```javascript
import { TimeFrame } from '@base-framework/ui/molecules';
TimeFrame({ dateTime: '2014-02-11T11:30:00' });
```

## Universal Icon System

```javascript
import { Icon, MaterialIcon, UniversalIcon, isMaterialIcon, isHeroicon } from '@base-framework/ui/atoms';
import { Icons, MaterialSymbols } from '@base-framework/ui/icons';

// UniversalIcon auto-detects icon type (recommended)
UniversalIcon({ size: 'md' }, Icons.home);                            // Heroicon SVG
UniversalIcon({ size: 'md' }, 'home');                                 // Material Symbol name
UniversalIcon({ size: 'md' }, MaterialSymbols.home);                   // Material Symbol
UniversalIcon({ size: 'md' }, { name: 'favorite', variant: 'filled' }); // With variant
```

**Detection Logic**: SVG string → `Icon`, Object with `.name` → `MaterialIcon`, plain string → `MaterialIcon`

**Material Symbol Variants**: `outlined` (default), `filled`, `rounded`, `sharp`

**Sizes**: xs (16px), sm (24px, default), md (32px), lg (40px), xl (48px), 2xl (56px), 3xl (64px)

**Helper Functions** (for custom components):
```javascript
isMaterialIcon('home');    // true
isHeroicon(Icons.home);    // true
```

**All components accepting `icon` prop support both systems automatically.**

## Button Variants

```javascript
import { Button, CircleButton, CircleToggleButton, LoadingButton, ToggleButton } from '@base-framework/ui/atoms';

// Standard variants — Atom, no `new`
Button({ variant: 'primary' }, 'Submit');
Button({ variant: 'secondary' }, 'Cancel');
Button({ variant: 'outline' }, 'Outline');
Button({ variant: 'ghost' }, 'Ghost');
Button({ variant: 'link' }, 'Link');
Button({ variant: 'destructive' }, 'Delete');
Button({ variant: 'warning' }, 'Warning');

// Icon variants
Button({ variant: 'icon', icon: Icons.settings });
Button({ variant: 'withIcon', icon: 'add' }, 'Add New');
Button({ variant: 'circleIcon', icon: 'home', size: 'md' }); // semi-transparent circular

// Back button — navigates back
Button({ variant: 'back', class: 'ghost', allowHistory: false });

// Toggle buttons (Component — use `new`)
new ToggleButton({ icon: 'heart', value: 234, toggle: (active) => {} });
new ToggleButton({ icon: 'heart', active: true, value: 234 }); // starts active
new ToggleButton({ icon: 'bookmark', activeIcon: 'bookmarkSolid' }); // swap icon
new ToggleButton({ icon: 'heart', dataKey: 'likeCount', toggle: (active) => {} }); // reactive count

// Circle buttons — frosted-glass (Atom, no `new`; sizes: xs|sm|md|lg|xl|2xl)
CircleButton({ icon: 'arrows.left', size: 'sm' });
CircleButton({ icon: 'share', size: 'md', click: () => {} });

// Circle toggle buttons (Component — use `new`)
new CircleToggleButton({ icon: 'heart', size: 'md', toggle: (active) => {} });
new CircleToggleButton({ icon: 'star', size: 'md', activeClass: 'text-yellow-400' });

// Loading button (Atom, no `new`)
LoadingButton('Saving…');
```

**CRITICAL**: No `variant: 'default'`. Primary CTA = `variant: 'primary'`.

## Design System Tokens (Rally) (CRITICAL)

**Surfaces** (additive layering):
- `bg-background` — base canvas (dark `#0b0b0c`)
- `bg-card` / `bg-popover` — surface 1 (dark `#121214`)
- `bg-surface-2` — raised cards / inputs / muted regions (dark `#18181b`)
- `bg-surface-3` — hovered / topmost layers (dark `#1f1f23`)
- `bg-accent-soft` — lime-accent low alpha for chips / selection

**Borders**:
- `border-border` — default hairline
- `border-border-strong` — hover / active hairline

**Card radius**: `rounded-card` (16px), `rounded-card-sm` (10px), `rounded-card-lg` (22px)

**Custom utilities**: `tabular` (tabular-nums), `hairline-t` / `hairline-b`, `placeholder-img`, `sheen`

**Fonts**: `font-sans` (Inter, with `'ss01','ss03','cv11'`), `font-display` (Instrument Serif italic), `font-mono` (JetBrains Mono), `font-mono-meta` (uppercase eyebrow mono)

**CRITICAL**:
- Never hardcode hex (`#0b0b0c`) or vendor colors (`bg-zinc-900`) — always use tokens
- Never use `border-white/10` — use `border-border` / `border-border-strong`
- These tokens cover light AND dark; the same component must work in both

## Shared Design-System Atoms (`@components/`)

Always check before building from scratch:

```javascript
import { MonoLabel } from '@components/atoms/typography/mono-label.js';
import { SerifDisplay } from '@components/atoms/typography/serif-display.js';
import { CTA } from '@components/atoms/cta.js';
import { Chip } from '@components/atoms/chip.js';
import { SectionDivider } from '@components/atoms/section-divider.js';
import { PlaceholderImage } from '@components/atoms/placeholder-image.js';
import { KeyValueRow } from '@components/atoms/key-value-row.js';
import { GlassIconButton } from '@components/atoms/buttons/glass-icon-button.js';
import { SectionHeader } from '@components/molecules/headers/section-header.js';
import { PageTitle } from '@components/molecules/headers/page-title.js';
import { EmptyStateDisplay } from '@components/molecules/empty-state-display.js';
```

| Atom | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `MonoLabel` | Small uppercase mono eyebrow / metadata |
| `SerifDisplay` | Instrument Serif italic for editorial titles |
| `CTA` | Pill-shaped CTA — `primary` \| `accent` \| `secondary` \| `ghost`; sizes `sm` \| `md` \| `lg`; opt `pill`, `monoMeta`, `fullWidth` |
| `Chip` | Filter/tag pill — `default` \| `accent` \| `outline`; renders Button when `click` provided |
| `SectionDivider` | Hairline divider between page sections |
| `PlaceholderImage` | Striped image slot, optional `shimmer`, optional centered mono label |
| `KeyValueRow` | Mono uppercase key + tabular value, `hairline-b` unless `last:true` |
| `GlassIconButton` | Frosted-glass icon button |
| `SectionHeader` | Numbered eyebrow + H2 + optional action |
| `PageTitle` | Page top header with eyebrow + title (`serif: true` for editorial italic) |
| `EmptyStateDisplay` | Serif italic empty state for content pages |

**CRITICAL**: There is no `editorial/` folder under `components/atoms` or `components/molecules` — these atoms ARE the app's base design system. Never create or import from `@components/atoms/editorial/...` or `@components/molecules/editorial/...`. Never prefix new tokens, classes, or files with `rally-`.

## Skeleton Components (CRITICAL)

**ALWAYS use Base UI `Skeleton`**, never raw `Div` with `bg-muted animate-pulse`.

```javascript
import { Skeleton } from '@base-framework/ui/atoms';

Skeleton({ shape: 'circle', width: 'size-10', height: 'size-10' })
Skeleton({ class: 'rounded-full', width: 'w-32' })
Skeleton({ class: 'aspect-square rounded-sm', width: 'w-full', height: 'h-auto' })
```

**RowSkeleton** — shared avatar + text lines pattern:
```javascript
import { RowSkeleton } from '@components/atoms/skeletons/row-skeleton.js';
RowSkeleton()
RowSkeleton({ avatarSize: 'size-12', lines: ['w-48', 'w-32', 'w-12'] })
RowSkeleton({ class: 'border-b border-border/50' })
```

## Shared Components (@components/)

**Location**: `apps/main/src/components/` (aliased as `@components/`)
Always check here BEFORE building a new component.

### Pill Bars
```javascript
import { PillTabBar } from '@components/molecules/pills/pill-tab-bar.js';
import { PillLinkBar } from '@components/molecules/pills/pill-link-bar.js';
import { StickyFilterBar } from '@components/organisms/sticky-filter-bar.js';

// State-driven (highlights based on reactive data key)
PillTabBar({ tabs: [{ label: 'All', value: 'all' }, ...], watchKey: 'activeFilter', onTabClick: (v) => this.data.activeFilter = v })

// Route-driven (highlights based on URL)
PillLinkBar({ tabs: [{ label: 'Followers', value: 'followers', href: './followers' }, ...], watchKey: 'activeTab' })

// Frosted-glass sticky wrapper
StickyFilterBar([PillTabBar({ ... })])
StickyFilterBar({ top: 'top-header-safe' }, [PillLinkBar({ ... })])
```

### User Display
```javascript
import { UserRow } from '@components/molecules/users/user-row.js';
